You took him from me. He loved me.

1067
01:29:41,509 --> 01:29:45,313
No. He despised you.

1068
01:29:45,446 --> 01:29:48,015
You were an embarrassment to him.

1069
01:29:49,317 --> 01:29:50,651
Oh.

1070
01:29:50,785 --> 01:29:53,921
Look at little Goblin Junior.

1071
01:29:54,055 --> 01:29:55,356
Gonna cry?

1072
01:29:55,490 --> 01:29:56,858
[GROWLS]

1073
01:30:10,037 --> 01:30:12,073
[BEEPING]

1074
01:30:31,893 --> 01:30:34,495
WOMAN: Spider-Man used to make me feel safe.

1075
01:30:34,629 --> 01:30:36,531
Now I'm afraid to walk home from work.

1076
01:30:36,664 --> 01:30:38,833
My son thought the world of this guy.

1077
01:30:38,966 --> 01:30:41,869
I have a 9-year-old daughter, loves Spider-Man. Who's she supposed to look up to now?

1078
01:30:42,003 --> 01:30:44,839
WOMAN: This is the guy they gave the key to the city to?

1079
01:30:44,972 --> 01:30:48,209
I'm gonna put some dirt in your eye.

1080
01:30:49,811 --> 01:30:51,612
MAN: Cheers to the new staff photographer.

1081
01:30:51,746 --> 01:30:53,147
Hey, I just got lucky.

1082
01:30:53,281 --> 01:30:54,982
This is so wonderful for you.

1083
01:30:55,116 --> 01:30:59,120
Well, you might wanna tell J.J. to make a little more wall space.

1084
01:31:03,791 --> 01:31:07,261
Well, good morning. It's a beautiful day, huh?

1085
01:31:07,395 --> 01:31:10,131
What was it you said? I'll never get that picture?

1086
01:31:10,264 --> 01:31:12,066
There's your hero.

1087
01:31:12,200 --> 01:31:14,068
Huh.

1088
01:31:14,202 --> 01:31:16,003
I never thought he'd really do that.

1089
01:31:16,137 --> 01:31:17,605
See? Right there.

1090
01:31:17,738 --> 01:31:20,508
You made a judgment call. You gotta see it as it is.

1091
01:31:20,641 --> 01:31:22,643
It's funny you should say that,

1092
01:31:22,777 --> 01:31:29,116
because I was looking through some old photos and it looks very, uh, similar.

1093
01:31:29,250 --> 01:31:32,720
Okay. Well, I gotta get back to work.

1094
01:31:33,688 --> 01:31:35,189
You're trash, Brock.

1095
01:31:35,323 --> 01:31:36,591
Excuse me?

1096
01:31:36,724 --> 01:31:39,060
Your picture's a fake.

1097
01:31:40,094 --> 01:31:43,798
Oh, Parker, you are such a boy scout.

1098
01:31:43,931 --> 01:31:45,933
When are you gonna give a guy a break?

1099
01:31:47,902 --> 01:31:50,905
You want forgiveness? Get religion.

1100
01:31:51,038 --> 01:31:54,275
What's going on here? Are you guys all right?

1101
01:31:57,044 --> 01:32:00,581
Yeah. No, we-- We're just horsing around.

1102
01:32:00,715 --> 01:32:04,986
Look, I'm begging you. If you do this, I will lose everything.

1103
01:32:05,119 --> 01:32:07,688
There's not a paper in town that will hire me.

1104
01:32:07,822 --> 01:32:10,625
You should've thought of that earlier.

1105
01:32:10,758 --> 01:32:12,927
ROBBIE: What are you doing, Peter?

1106
01:32:13,060 --> 01:32:17,765
Show this to your editor. Tell him to check his source next time.

1107
01:32:23,571 --> 01:32:25,006
ROBBIE: It's a fake.

1108
01:32:25,139 --> 01:32:29,710
Empire State Photographic Department confirms it.

1109
01:32:32,947 --> 01:32:34,782
Pack your things. Get out of my building.

1110
01:32:34,916 --> 01:32:39,153
I was just trying-- You're fired.

1111
01:32:39,287 --> 01:32:41,255
ROBBIE: You know we're gonna have to print a retraction now.

1112
01:32:41,389 --> 01:32:43,391
I haven't printed a retraction in 20 years.

1113
01:32:43,524 --> 01:32:47,261
[JAMES BROWN'S "PEOPLE GET UP AND DRIVE YOUR FUNKY SOUL" PLAYING]

1114
01:32:48,229 --> 01:32:49,830
[PHONE RINGS]

1115
01:32:49,964 --> 01:32:51,132
Hello.

1116
01:32:51,265 --> 01:32:52,500
CONNORS: Mr. Parker, Dr. Connors here.

1117
01:32:52,633 --> 01:32:55,970
Oh, Dr. Connors. How are you?

1118
01:32:56,103 --> 01:32:57,104
[SNORES]

1119
01:32:57,238 --> 01:33:00,308
Quite a specimen you left me, Parker.

1120
01:33:00,441 --> 01:33:05,246
Its chemistry is not unlike the chondritic meteorites of the '70s.

1121
01:33:05,379 --> 01:33:06,614
Thanks.

1122
01:33:06,747 --> 01:33:08,215
Mmm. That's good.

1123
01:33:08,349 --> 01:33:09,684
You know what, Parker?

1124
01:33:11,252 --> 01:33:12,119
Parker?

1125
01:33:12,253 --> 01:33:14,255
Get me some milk.

1126
01:33:14,388 --> 01:33:18,359
It amplifies characteristics of its host.

1127
01:33:18,492 --> 01:33:19,694
Hey, give me another cookie.

1128
01:33:19,827 --> 01:33:22,663
Especially aggression.

1129
01:33:22,797 --> 01:33:24,865
This could be dangerous.

1130
01:33:24,999 --> 01:33:28,736
Peter, you didn't keep any, did you?

1131
01:33:28,869 --> 01:33:30,071
You got any with nuts?

1132
01:33:30,204 --> 01:33:32,607
I have some nuts. I could make some.

1133
01:33:32,740 --> 01:33:34,542
Go make me some. Peter?

1134
01:33:34,675 --> 01:33:37,378
No, no, no. Course not.

1135
01:33:51,626 --> 01:33:53,127
These shots are so good.

1136
01:33:53,260 --> 01:33:56,631
I'd love to shoot you sometime.

1137
01:33:56,764 --> 01:33:59,700
Peter Parker. Peter.

1138
01:33:59,834 --> 01:34:04,672
Parker! Miss Brant, that's not the position I hired you for.

1139
01:34:04,805 --> 01:34:06,440
Black-suit Spider-Man.

1140
01:34:07,808 --> 01:34:09,844
Peter, these are incredible.

1141
01:34:09,977 --> 01:34:11,812
We gotta have these, Jonah.

1142
01:34:11,946 --> 01:34:13,280
I'll pay you the usual rate.

1143
01:34:14,849 --> 01:34:17,418
If you want the shots, I'll take the staff job,

1144
01:34:17,551 --> 01:34:19,787
double the money.

1145
01:35:44,038 --> 01:35:46,340
MARKO: Penny.

1146
01:35:52,046 --> 01:35:55,816
You are really gonna dig this joint.

1147
01:35:55,950 --> 01:35:58,052
Do you think I'm--? I'm dressed all right?

1148
01:35:58,185 --> 01:35:59,854
Too fancy or too...?

1149
01:35:59,987 --> 01:36:03,724
Are you kidding me? You're looking fine, babe.

1150
01:36:03,858 --> 01:36:05,259
GWEN: Thank you.

1151
01:36:05,392 --> 01:36:06,193
[GWEN GIGGLES]

1152
01:36:06,327 --> 01:36:08,496
PETER: Love that little giggle.

1153
01:36:10,664 --> 01:36:12,466
Hey, keep it open there, pops.

1154
01:36:12,600 --> 01:36:15,836
[BAND PLAYING AND WOMAN SINGING "L-O-V-E"]

1155
01:36:15,970 --> 01:36:19,206
Oh, this is so cool.

1156
01:36:19,340 --> 01:36:22,476
I have never been to a jazz club before.

1157
01:36:25,045 --> 01:36:28,582
Oh, I hope we can get a table.

1158
01:36:29,350 --> 01:36:31,018
[WHISTLES]

1159
01:36:33,120 --> 01:36:35,890
Find us some shade.

1160
01:36:36,690 --> 01:36:39,059
Thanks, hot legs.

1161
01:36:39,193 --> 01:36:42,029
Right this way, sir.

1162
01:36:49,103 --> 01:36:51,472
Oh, why, thank you.

1163
01:36:54,975 --> 01:36:56,377
[CROWD APPLAUDING]

1164
01:36:56,510 --> 01:36:58,279
I am so loving this.

1165
01:36:58,412 --> 01:37:00,481
Oh, me too.

1166
01:37:00,614 --> 01:37:02,416
[SONG ENDS]

1167
01:37:05,920 --> 01:37:07,721
Isn't that your old girlfriend?

1168
01:37:07,855 --> 01:37:09,256
Yeah.

1169
01:37:09,390 --> 01:37:11,025
Do you wanna go someplace else?

1170
01:37:11,158 --> 01:37:13,694
Oh, no, no. I'll-- I'll be okay.

1171
01:37:13,828 --> 01:37:16,430
Mary Jane, show us what you got. MAN: I'll take that.

1172
01:37:16,564 --> 01:37:18,933
[BAND PLAYING "FEVER"]

1173
01:37:22,670 --> 01:37:23,938
I'll be right back.

1174
01:37:24,071 --> 01:37:26,073
All right.

1175
01:37:32,112 --> 01:37:34,548
[PIANO PLAYING]

1176
01:37:34,682 --> 01:37:36,350
MARY JANE: Peter?

1177
01:37:39,019 --> 01:37:40,387
This is for you.

1178
01:37:46,660 --> 01:37:48,562
Double-time.

1179
01:37:53,567 --> 01:37:55,569
Thanks.

1180
01:37:55,703 --> 01:37:58,038
[CROWD CHEERING]

1181
01:38:21,896 --> 01:38:24,231
[WHISPERS]: Now dig on this.

1182
01:38:24,999 --> 01:38:26,533
WOMAN: That is hot.

1183
01:38:31,972 --> 01:38:34,108
CROWD: Ooh.

1184
01:38:58,065 --> 01:39:01,001
[CROWD APPLAUDING AND CHEERING]

1185
01:39:07,308 --> 01:39:09,443
That was all for her?

1186
01:39:11,512 --> 01:39:14,715
[BAND PLAYING "STORMY WEATHER"]

1187
01:39:17,818 --> 01:39:19,586
I'm so sorry.

1188
01:39:31,765 --> 01:39:33,033
You all right, Mary Jane?

1189
01:39:33,167 --> 01:39:34,401
I'm fine.

1190
01:39:34,535 --> 01:39:36,103
Okay.

1191
01:39:38,772 --> 01:39:40,174
Hey.

1192
01:39:42,376 --> 01:39:44,211
What's wrong with you?

1193
01:39:45,112 --> 01:39:46,380
You.

1194
01:39:47,047 --> 01:39:48,282
Can I help you, sir?

1195
01:39:48,415 --> 01:39:50,050
No.

1196
01:39:50,184 --> 01:39:52,086
Is everything okay here, Paul?

1197
01:39:52,219 --> 01:39:54,488
Yeah, is everything okay here, Paul?

1198
01:39:54,621 --> 01:39:57,091
Take him out of here. BOUNCER: Let's go, sir.

1199
01:39:57,224 --> 01:40:00,060
Take your hand off of me. BOUNCER: Now.

1200
01:40:00,194 --> 01:40:04,198
Okay. Hey, get off! Let go!

1201
01:40:06,300 --> 01:40:07,735
Peter, stop it!

1202
01:40:19,613 --> 01:40:21,348
Who are you?

1203
01:40:23,350 --> 01:40:25,252
I don't know.

1204
01:40:51,779 --> 01:40:55,182
[CHURCH BELL TOLLING]

1205
01:41:02,322 --> 01:41:04,691
[THUNDER CRASHING]

1206
01:41:38,225 --> 01:41:40,594
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

1207
01:41:57,344 --> 01:41:59,680
BROCK: It's Brock, sir.

1208
01:41:59,813 --> 01:42:02,583
Edward Brock Jr.

1209
01:42:03,917 --> 01:42:06,587
I come before you today...

1210
01:42:07,855 --> 01:42:09,890
humbled...

1211
01:42:11,458 --> 01:42:13,694
and humiliated...

1212
01:42:16,430 --> 01:42:18,899
to ask you for one thing.

1213
01:42:24,304 --> 01:42:26,573
I want you to kill Peter Parker.

1214
01:42:27,941 --> 01:42:30,344
[SPIDER-MAN GRUNTING]

1215
01:42:38,819 --> 01:42:39,786
[BELL TOLLING]

1216
01:42:39,920 --> 01:42:41,622
[SYMBIOTE SCREECHING]

1217
01:42:46,927 --> 01:42:49,329
[BELL TOLLING]

1218
01:42:53,967 --> 01:42:56,336
[SCREAMING]

1219
01:42:58,906 --> 01:43:01,275
[PETER YELLING]

1220
01:43:04,478 --> 01:43:06,813
[PETER GRUNTING]

1221
01:43:10,884 --> 01:43:13,287
[PETER SCREAMING]

1222
01:43:17,124 --> 01:43:18,625
Parker.

1223
01:43:23,297 --> 01:43:25,766
[SCREAMING] [SYMBIOTE SCREECHING]

1224
01:43:44,952 --> 01:43:47,688
[YELLING]

1225
01:43:52,960 --> 01:43:55,329
[BROCK GRUNTING]

1226
01:44:01,868 --> 01:44:03,837
[HEAVING]

1227
01:44:10,410 --> 01:44:11,745
[SCREECHES]

1228
01:44:27,594 --> 01:44:29,363
[HANDLE SQUEAKS]

1229
01:44:42,442 --> 01:44:43,977
[KNOCKS]

1230
01:44:48,081 --> 01:44:49,750
[KNOCKS]

1231
01:45:02,129 --> 01:45:04,831
Hi, Peter. Hi.

1232
01:45:05,799 --> 01:45:07,134
Hmm.

1233
01:45:07,267 --> 01:45:11,138
You don't seem to have changed the room around very much.

1234
01:45:11,271 --> 01:45:16,610
Of course, there's not much you could do, is there?

1235
01:45:22,449 --> 01:45:24,551
When we spoke on the phone,

1236
01:45:24,685 --> 01:45:27,287
I sensed that something was bothering you,

1237
01:45:27,421 --> 01:45:31,758
so I thought I'd just come by.

1238
01:45:33,627 --> 01:45:36,396
How's Mary Jane?

1239
01:45:36,530 --> 01:45:38,565
I don't know.

1240
01:45:40,634 --> 01:45:43,136
I never heard from you.

1241
01:45:43,270 --> 01:45:46,039
Did you ever propose?

1242
01:45:49,943 --> 01:45:52,479
You said...

1243
01:45:52,612 --> 01:45:55,849
a husband's gotta put a wife before himself.

1244
01:46:01,021 --> 01:46:03,123
I'm not ready.

1245
01:46:05,492 --> 01:46:08,061
But what happened?

1246
01:46:08,195 --> 01:46:11,131
You seemed so sure.

1247
01:46:12,132 --> 01:46:14,000
Yeah.

1248
01:46:15,135 --> 01:46:17,003
I, uh...

1249
01:46:27,147 --> 01:46:29,616
I hurt her, Aunt May.

1250
01:46:30,717 --> 01:46:33,053
I don't know what to do.

1251
01:46:34,654 --> 01:46:39,092
Well, you start by doing the hardest thing:

1252
01:46:39,226 --> 01:46:42,496
You forgive yourself.

1253
01:46:45,332 --> 01:46:47,968
I believe in you, Peter.

1254
01:46:48,101 --> 01:46:51,705
You're a good person.

1255
01:46:51,838 --> 01:46:57,110
And I know you will find a way to put it right.

1256
01:47:04,618 --> 01:47:06,653
In time.

1257
01:47:24,137 --> 01:47:27,007
MARKO: End of the line, Spider-Man.

1258
01:47:27,140 --> 01:47:29,075
[SCREECHES]

1259
01:47:30,811 --> 01:47:33,046
I want him dead too, Flint.

1260
01:47:33,180 --> 01:47:35,816
That's why I've been looking for you.

1261
01:47:35,949 --> 01:47:39,286
Oh, yeah. I know all about you.

1262
01:47:39,419 --> 01:47:43,824
Like the fact that Spider-Man won't let you help your poor daughter.

1263
01:47:43,957 --> 01:47:47,194
It's just-- That doesn't seem right to me.

1264
01:47:47,327 --> 01:47:52,499
Look, I wanna kill the spider, you wanna kill the spider.

1265
01:47:52,632 --> 01:47:56,169
Together, he doesn't stand a chance.

1266
01:47:57,070 --> 01:47:59,239
Interested?

1267
01:48:00,340 --> 01:48:02,175
Yeah.

1268
01:49:03,803 --> 01:49:05,005
EDDIE: So...

1269
01:49:05,138 --> 01:49:08,842
where to?

1270
01:49:08,975 --> 01:49:10,744
All New York is holding its breath

1271
01:49:10,877 --> 01:49:13,647
as the hostage crisis continues to unfold.

1272
01:49:14,814 --> 01:49:16,216
REPORTER: Just 30 minutes ago,

1273
01:49:16,349 --> 01:49:18,552
police came across this startling sight:

1274
01:49:18,685 --> 01:49:20,687
A young woman, held hostage in a taxi

1275
01:49:20,820 --> 01:49:22,989
suspended 80 stories above the ground

1276
01:49:23,123 --> 01:49:25,692
in what appears to be a giant web.

1277
01:49:25,825 --> 01:49:28,962
ANCHORMAN: Every attempt by the police to rescue the hostage

1278
01:49:29,095 --> 01:49:31,264
has been thwarted by the Sandman.

1279
01:49:31,398 --> 01:49:33,833
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

1280
01:49:33,967 --> 01:49:38,438
Compounding the danger is the appearance of a strange black-suited figure.

1281
01:49:38,572 --> 01:49:42,309
Early reports had believed him to be the black-suited Spider-Man,

1282
01:49:42,442 --> 01:49:46,646
but he has now been identified as something entirely different.

1283
01:49:46,780 --> 01:49:48,548
[VENOM SCREECHES ON TV]

1284
01:49:48,682 --> 01:49:51,384
The hostage has been identified as Mary Jane Watson,

1285
01:49:51,518 --> 01:49:56,222
an actress recently seen in a brief stint on Broadway.

1286
01:50:21,314 --> 01:50:23,817
We're now going to take you live to the scene,

1287
01:50:23,950 --> 01:50:25,852
with Jennifer Dugan. Jennifer?

1288
01:50:25,986 --> 01:50:28,455
We're only about a hundred feet away now, Hal, and--

1289
01:50:28,588 --> 01:50:32,425
Wait. There seems to be some kind of activity in the web.

1290
01:50:32,559 --> 01:50:36,696
They seem to be creating some kind of gigantic lettering.

1291
01:50:38,932 --> 01:50:41,935
Apparently, Spider-Man's being challenged to some sort of confrontation.

1292
01:50:42,068 --> 01:50:43,870
And that raises serious questions

1293
01:50:44,004 --> 01:50:47,707
about what kind of chance he'd stand against such overwhelming--

1294
01:50:57,784 --> 01:50:59,419
PETER: Harry?

1295
01:51:02,756 --> 01:51:04,691
I need your help.

1296
01:51:04,824 --> 01:51:08,862
I can't take them both, not by myself.

1297
01:51:15,035 --> 01:51:18,204
You don't deserve my help.

1298
01:51:20,840 --> 01:51:22,442
Harry...

1299
01:51:22,942 --> 01:51:25,278
she needs us.

1300
01:51:29,549 --> 01:51:31,384
Get out.

1301
01:51:47,734 --> 01:51:50,437
BERNARD: If I may, sir?

1302
01:51:50,570 --> 01:51:56,109
I've seen things in this house I've never spoken of.

1303
01:51:56,242 --> 01:51:58,478
What are you trying to tell me?

1304
01:51:58,611 --> 01:52:01,948
The night your father died,

1305
01:52:02,082 --> 01:52:04,884
I cleaned his wound.

1306
01:52:06,019 --> 01:52:09,756
The blade that pierced his body

1307
01:52:09,889 --> 01:52:12,358
came from his glider.

1308
01:52:12,492 --> 01:52:18,031
I know you're trying to defend your father's honor,

1309
01:52:18,164 --> 01:52:23,937
but there's no question that he died by his own hand.

1310
01:52:26,906 --> 01:52:29,509
I loved your father...

1311
01:52:30,577 --> 01:52:33,913
as I have loved you, Harry.

1312
01:52:34,047 --> 01:52:37,150
As your friends love you.

1313
01:52:56,636 --> 01:52:59,038
[RATTLING AND CREAKING]

1314
01:53:03,576 --> 01:53:05,979
[CREAKING]

1315
01:53:10,483 --> 01:53:12,385
[SCREAMING]

1316
01:53:16,389 --> 01:53:18,291
[CROWD GASPS]

1317
01:53:24,264 --> 01:53:25,565
Look.

1318
01:53:37,477 --> 01:53:40,346
[CROWD CHEERING]

1319
01:53:45,919 --> 01:53:50,023
CROWD [CHANTING]: Spider-Man! Spider-Man! Spider-Man!

1320
01:53:55,195 --> 01:53:57,063
He seems to have come out of nowhere

1321
01:53:57,197 --> 01:53:59,199
to answer the prayers of the city,

1322
01:53:59,332 --> 01:54:01,935
just when all hope seemed to be lost.

1323
01:54:07,307 --> 01:54:10,343
Peter. They're gonna kill us both.

1324
01:54:10,476 --> 01:54:11,878
I'm gonna get you out of this.

1325
01:54:12,011 --> 01:54:12,946
Watch out!

1326
01:54:13,079 --> 01:54:14,480
[VENOM SCREECHES]

1327
01:54:17,083 --> 01:54:19,385
[GRUNTING]

1328
01:54:23,623 --> 01:54:24,924
Hey, Parker.

1329
01:54:25,058 --> 01:54:26,292
SPIDER-MAN: My God. Eddie.

1330
01:54:26,426 --> 01:54:29,095
Ooh, my spider-sense is tingling,

1331
01:54:30,263 --> 01:54:33,499
if you know what I'm talking about.

1332
01:54:36,569 --> 01:54:37,670
[CROWD GASPING]

1333
01:54:47,080 --> 01:54:49,382
[MARY JANE SCREAMS]

1334
01:54:52,218 --> 01:54:54,354
We can find a way to settle this.

1335
01:54:54,487 --> 01:54:55,889
You're so right.

1336
01:54:56,022 --> 01:54:59,959
I'm thinking humiliation.

1337
01:55:00,093 --> 01:55:02,695
Kind of like how you humiliated me.

1338
01:55:03,496 --> 01:55:05,431
Do you remember?

1339
01:55:06,733 --> 01:55:09,636
Do you remember what you did to me?

1340
01:55:10,803 --> 01:55:13,339
[METAL CREAKING]

1341
01:55:24,851 --> 01:55:29,155
You made me lose my girl. Now I'm gonna make you lose yours.

1342
01:55:30,790 --> 01:55:33,159
How's that sound, tiger?

1343
01:55:35,728 --> 01:55:37,163
[SCREECHING]

1344
01:56:14,667 --> 01:56:16,469
[METAL CREAKING]

1345
01:56:17,804 --> 01:56:19,772
[GASPING]

1346
01:56:32,452 --> 01:56:34,554
Hold on, Mary Jane!

1347
01:56:50,169 --> 01:56:52,038
[CROWD SCREAMING]

1348
01:56:52,171 --> 01:56:54,540
[SANDMAN GROWLING]

1349
01:57:02,815 --> 01:57:04,384
[MARY JANE WHIMPERS]

1350
01:57:04,517 --> 01:57:07,086
Mary Jane!

1351
01:57:14,827 --> 01:57:16,829
[SCREAMING]

1352
01:57:27,807 --> 01:57:30,543
[SPIDER-MAN GRUNTING]

1353
01:57:43,589 --> 01:57:45,725
[ROARING]

1354
01:57:53,599 --> 01:57:54,767
[LAUGHS]

1355
01:58:07,180 --> 01:58:11,084
It's hard to believe what's happening.

1356
01:58:11,217 --> 01:58:14,120
The brutality of it.

1357
01:58:14,253 --> 01:58:15,888
I don't know how he can take any more.

1358
01:58:16,022 --> 01:58:19,392
This could be a tragic day for the people of New York.

1359
01:58:19,525 --> 01:58:22,195
It could be the end of Spider-Man.

1360
01:58:37,610 --> 01:58:39,479
Hm?

1361
01:58:39,612 --> 01:58:41,547
[BEEPING]

1362
01:58:45,551 --> 01:58:48,187
[SANDMAN ROARING]

1363
01:58:48,321 --> 01:58:49,222
Awesome.

1364
01:58:49,355 --> 01:58:50,890
Wicked cool.

1365
01:59:15,681 --> 01:59:17,316
You came.

1366
01:59:24,757 --> 01:59:26,425
Looks like just in the nick of time.

1367
01:59:26,559 --> 01:59:29,829
A couple minutes ago wouldn't have been so bad either.

1368
01:59:29,962 --> 01:59:31,464
What are you gonna do?

1369
01:59:31,597 --> 01:59:34,634
[VENOM SCREECHING]

1370
01:59:34,767 --> 01:59:36,903
I may need some help over here.

1371
01:59:37,036 --> 01:59:39,772
I'm a little busy right now.

1372
01:59:40,540 --> 01:59:42,708
Give me your hand.

1373
01:59:48,548 --> 01:59:50,650
[SANDMAN GROWLING]

1374
01:59:55,354 --> 01:59:56,756
[CROWD GASPING]

1375
01:59:56,889 --> 01:59:59,559
Parker! Parker, where--?

1376
01:59:59,692 --> 02:00:01,394
I need a photographer.

1377
02:00:01,527 --> 02:00:02,762
Hey, kid, you want a job?

1378
02:00:02,895 --> 02:00:06,365
Why would I want a job? I'm just a kid.

1379
02:00:06,499 --> 02:00:08,201
All right, how much for the camera?

1380
02:00:08,334 --> 02:00:09,669
One hundred bucks.

1381
02:00:09,802 --> 02:00:11,270
A hundred bucks?

1382
02:00:11,404 --> 02:00:12,572
[CROWD GASPING]

1383
02:00:12,705 --> 02:00:16,976
All right, you little crook. Here.

1384
02:00:18,511 --> 02:00:20,012
What the--?

1385
02:00:21,881 --> 02:00:23,749
Film's extra.

1386
02:00:29,355 --> 02:00:31,357
Gotcha.

1387
02:00:35,428 --> 02:00:36,996
[METAL CLICKS] [GASPS]

1388
02:00:39,131 --> 02:00:40,733
Pete, up top!

1389
02:00:44,070 --> 02:00:46,405
[SCREAMS]

1390
02:00:58,584 --> 02:01:00,019
[SCREAMING]

1391
02:01:00,152 --> 02:01:02,488
SPIDER-MAN: Mary Jane.

1392
02:01:04,423 --> 02:01:06,325
This thing got any more? Hang on!

1393
02:01:06,459 --> 02:01:07,860
To what?

1394
02:01:11,998 --> 02:01:14,000
Go, buddy! Got her!

1395
02:01:18,237 --> 02:01:20,473
[CHEERING]

1396
02:01:25,077 --> 02:01:26,445
You okay?

1397
02:01:28,214 --> 02:01:30,049
Yeah.

1398
02:01:32,752 --> 02:01:33,919
Good.

1399
02:01:34,053 --> 02:01:37,056
HARRY: Hey, Pete! [SANDMAN ROARING]

1400
02:01:37,189 --> 02:01:39,392
Am I interrupting?

1401
02:01:56,075 --> 02:01:58,477
[CROWD SCREAMING]

1402
02:02:06,986 --> 02:02:09,822
[ROARING]

1403
02:02:21,033 --> 02:02:23,402
[CROWD CHEERING]

1404
02:02:24,770 --> 02:02:26,872
[VENOM SCREECHES]

1405
02:02:31,510 --> 02:02:32,611
[METAL SQUEAKS]

1406
02:02:32,745 --> 02:02:35,147
[GROWLING AND SCREECHING IN DISTANCE]

1407
02:02:39,585 --> 02:02:41,987
[HEAVY BREATHING]

1408
02:02:47,226 --> 02:02:49,395
[VENOM SCREECHING]

1409
02:02:55,267 --> 02:02:57,470
Never wound...

1410
02:02:58,070 --> 02:03:00,406
what you can't kill.

1411
02:03:03,743 --> 02:03:07,413
Eddie, the suit, you gotta take it off.

1412
02:03:07,546 --> 02:03:09,515
Oh, you'd like that, wouldn't you?

1413
02:03:12,184 --> 02:03:14,086
I know what it feels like.

1414
02:03:14,587 --> 02:03:16,155
It feels good.

1415
02:03:16,288 --> 02:03:18,758
The power. Everything.

1416
02:03:18,891 --> 02:03:21,727
But you'll lose yourself.

1417
02:03:21,861 --> 02:03:24,029
Let it go.

1418
02:03:24,163 --> 02:03:26,499
I like being bad.

1419
02:03:27,266 --> 02:03:29,435
It makes me happy.

1420
02:03:34,140 --> 02:03:35,474
[SCREECHES]

1421
02:03:45,351 --> 02:03:46,952
[POLES CHIMING]

1422
02:03:47,086 --> 02:03:49,655
[VENOM SCREAMING]

1423
02:03:50,689 --> 02:03:52,925
[SYMBIOTE SCREECHING]

1424
02:03:55,294 --> 02:03:57,963
[BELL TOLLING] [SYMBIOTE SCREECHING]

1425
02:04:01,200 --> 02:04:03,035
[VENOM SCREECHING]

1426
02:04:18,617 --> 02:04:19,985
Harry!

1427
02:04:42,041 --> 02:04:44,243
[POLES CHIMING]

1428
02:04:44,376 --> 02:04:46,912
[YELLING]

1429
02:05:00,226 --> 02:05:02,695
[SYMBIOTE SCREECHING]

1430
02:05:03,262 --> 02:05:05,631
[BROCK SCREAMING]

1431
02:05:12,938 --> 02:05:15,708
[SYMBIOTE WAILING]

1432
02:05:26,285 --> 02:05:28,153
[SCREECHING]

1433
02:05:32,691 --> 02:05:34,927
Peter! What are you doing?!

1434
02:05:36,128 --> 02:05:38,130
No!

1435
02:05:39,632 --> 02:05:41,000
Eddie!

1436
02:06:00,653 --> 02:06:01,921
Harry. Mary Jane.

1437
02:06:02,054 --> 02:06:04,290
I'm gonna get help. No.

1438
02:06:05,057 --> 02:06:06,659
Stay.

1439
02:06:14,867 --> 02:06:17,670
MARKO: I didn't want this.

1440
02:06:21,640 --> 02:06:24,143
But I had no choice.

1441
02:06:27,513 --> 02:06:29,415
We always have a choice.

1442
02:06:29,548 --> 02:06:32,284
You had a choice when you killed my uncle.

1443
02:06:34,520 --> 02:06:36,355
My daughter was dying.

1444
02:06:38,791 --> 02:06:40,826
I needed money.

1445
02:06:45,364 --> 02:06:47,700
I was scared.

1446
02:06:54,506 --> 02:06:57,843
I told your uncle all I wanted was the car.

1447
02:06:57,977 --> 02:07:00,179
What is it? MARKO: I need your car.

1448
02:07:00,312 --> 02:07:02,881
He said to me,

1449
02:07:03,015 --> 02:07:06,251
"Why don't you just put down the gun and go home?"

1450
02:07:09,722 --> 02:07:13,325
I realize now he was just trying to help me.

1451
02:07:19,465 --> 02:07:22,735
Then I saw my partner running over with the cash.

1452
02:07:22,868 --> 02:07:24,169
And the gun was in my hand.

1453
02:07:24,303 --> 02:07:25,671
[GUNSHOT]

1454
02:07:35,848 --> 02:07:37,416
Get in!

1455
02:07:38,917 --> 02:07:42,721
MARKO: Did a terrible thing to you...

1456
02:07:42,855 --> 02:07:46,425
and I spent a lot of nights wishing I could take it back.

1457
02:07:51,263 --> 02:07:54,867
I'm not asking you to forgive me.

1458
02:07:55,000 --> 02:07:57,703
I just want you to understand.

1459
02:08:07,046 --> 02:08:10,149
I've done terrible things too.

1460
02:08:21,460 --> 02:08:24,730
[CROWD CHEERING BELOW]

1461
02:08:25,998 --> 02:08:29,201
MARKO: I didn't choose to be this.

1462
02:08:37,242 --> 02:08:40,345
The only thing left of me now...

1463
02:08:42,347 --> 02:08:44,383
is my daughter.

1464
02:08:56,395 --> 02:08:58,497
I forgive you.

1465
02:09:41,673 --> 02:09:44,576
Hey, pal. How you doing?

1466
02:09:44,710 --> 02:09:46,578
Been better.

1467
02:09:47,980 --> 02:09:50,282
We'll get you through this.

1468
02:09:53,619 --> 02:09:55,420
No.

1469
02:10:02,694 --> 02:10:05,297
I should never have hurt you...

1470
02:10:06,899 --> 02:10:09,401
said those things.

1471
02:10:10,435 --> 02:10:13,572
HARRY: None of that matters, Peter.

1472
02:10:15,474 --> 02:10:17,442
You're my friend.

1473
02:10:21,980 --> 02:10:24,016
Best friend.

1474
02:10:42,601 --> 02:10:44,536
Harry.

1475
02:11:30,182 --> 02:11:32,317
PETER: Whatever comes our way,

1476
02:11:32,451 --> 02:11:38,023
whatever battle we have raging inside us, we always have a choice.

1477
02:11:39,324 --> 02:11:41,627
My friend Harry taught me that.

1478
02:11:41,760 --> 02:11:45,697
He chose to be the best of himself.

1479
02:11:45,831 --> 02:11:48,800
It's the choices that make us who we are,

1480
02:11:48,934 --> 02:11:53,071
and we can always choose to do what's right.

1481
02:11:54,606 --> 02:11:58,143
[PIANO PLAYING]

1482
02:12:01,179 --> 02:12:04,583
[SINGING "I'M THRU WITH LOVE"]

1483
02:12:25,771 --> 02:12:28,407
[BAND PLAYING]

1484
02:13:58,497 --> 02:14:01,666
[INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC]

1485
02:14:38,570 --> 02:14:42,240
[SNOW PATROL'S "SIGNAL FIRE" PLAYING]

1486
02:16:35,287 --> 02:16:38,790
[THE KILLERS' "MOVE AWAY" PLAYING]

1487
02:17:46,391 --> 02:17:49,761
[JET'S "FALLING STAR" PLAYING]

1488
02:19:04,369 --> 02:19:06,538
[SONG ENDS]

